{
  "text": "} (note that we changed the coloring of the edges from black/gray in [CITATION_1] to red/black, because this corresponds to the colors we use in the multiple breakpoint graph). An example of a breakpoint graph is given in Fig. 1 (u, v) and (x, y) (with u < v and x < y) intersect if u < x < v < y or x < u < y < v. Two cycles intersect if they have intersecting black edges.",
